In this example, the `handleButtonClick` function is memoized using `useCallback`. It prevents the `handleButtonClick` function from being re-created on every render of the `ParentComponent`. This is useful to avoid unnecessary re-renders of the `ClickButton` component since the `handleButtonClick` prop remains the same as long as the `count` state does not change.

These are some of the widely used React hooks along with simple explanations and code examples for each. Please note that the availability and usage of hooks may change in newer versions of React, and there might be additional hooks introduced in

